El-Erian Says S&P Will Downgrade U.S. If They Stick to Outlook

-- B y   D a v e   L i e d t k a
-- 
2011-08-03T13:16:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/el-erian-says-s-p-will-downgrade-u-s-if-they-stick-to-outlook.html
Standard & Poor’s  will downgrade the
U.S. if the credit-rating company sticks to what it outlined
last month, according to Pacific Investment Management Co.’s
Mohamed El-Erian.  El-Erian, chief executive and co-chief investment officer
at the world’s biggest manager of bond funds, made the comment
in an interview on Bloomberg Television’s “In the Loop” with
Betty Liu.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dave Liedtka at   dliedtka@bloomberg.net  